    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We plan to observe the ground state transition of deuterated molecular hydrogen (HD) toward a dusty galaxy at z = 5.656. The line is predicted to be detectable in emission. These observations will provide the total amount of HD molecules and, through the HD/H2 abundance ratio given by the cosmic abundance of deuterium, the total molecular gas mass, independent on uncertainties plaguing other standard methods. If successful, this data will open a new way to measure masses of molecular gas in the Universe and it can be used to calibrate the CO to H2 conversion factor and dust emission methods.</prp:abstract>
